31 Aug 2018 22:24






I have to downvote. It'sa collection of random unexplained events that doesn't tie together in any way. There's no narrative here, when there was clearly intended to be a narrative. Dude disappeared. Cabin gives people a worse version of Locked-in Syndrome. It inexplicably expands, because we need to meet our quota of Foundation slaughter. There's a letter that has no explanation or relevance to the rest of the story. And then suddenly it's over because Anomalous Jack randomly attacks a researcher for no clear reason.

These are all checkpoints in an outline. But that's all that's there. Nothing fills it in. We don't even know why Anomalous Jack calls it  It feels like this could go somewhere interesting, but as it currently stands, it's not.







